{{Quote|Narwotha inside kineesh! Help! Darr tah!|A crazed [[Alien/Legends|alien]], after being driven insane by Rakata technology|<ref name="Star Wars: The Old Republic">''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]''</ref>}}
'''Rakata''',<ref name="Kotor" /> or '''Rakatan''',<ref name="JvS">[[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']]</ref> was the [[Language/Legends|language]] spoken by the [[Rakata/Legends|Rakata]]. When [[Revan/Legends|Revan]] was seeking the [[Star Forge]] the first [[Time/Legends|time]], [[Gender/Legends|he]] learned the language by [[Drain Knowledge|ripping]] the knowledge from [[the One]], leader of a primitive [[Black Rakata|Rakatan tribe]]. Upon returning during the quest to destroy the Star Forge, Revan found he still retained his knowledge of the language despite having had his [[Memory wipe/Legends|memory wiped]] by the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi Council]].<ref name="Kotor" />

Some [[Historian/Legends|historians]] believed that [[Darth/Legends|''Darth'']] was derived either from the Rakatan word ''[[Daritha]]'' ([[Emperor/Legends|emperor]]) or from the Rakatan words ''darr'' (victory) and ''tah'' ([[Death/Legends|death]]). Combined, the phrase ''[[darr tah]]'' meant victory over death, immortal, or conquest through the death of one's enemies.<ref name="JvS" />

